The Project editor consists of three main areas:

![](data:image/png;base64,)Project editor

- **Project toolbar** with menu and action buttons for creating Mappings and Productions

- **Scene and pop-up sidebar **with a palette of scenes and pop-ups

- **Storyboard editor** for connecting individual scenes and pop-ups

## Project toolbar
The Project toolbar provides general navigation, Project management buttons and quick access to key actions.

![](data:image/png;base64,)Project toolbar

- **Hamburger menu**

**Go to Projects:** Returns to the main [Projects](/doxee-platform/docs/projects-user-interface) tab

- **Project settings:** Opens the [settings](/doxee-platform/docs/pvideo-designer-project-settings-user-interface) of this Project

- **Duplicate project:** Creates a copy of the current Project

- **Delete Project:** Deletes the current Project

- **Breadcrumb bar**

**Projects:** Returns to the main Projects tab

- **Project name:** View and change the name of the Project

- **Copy icon:** Copies the UUID of the Project to the clipboard

- **Action buttons**

**Data Mapper:** Create a new data schema or apply an existing schema to this Project

- **Production:** Create a static video without a data schema or open the Production pipeline to generate a dynamic interactive video

- **User information**

**Legacy Platform:** Switch to the legacy Babelee platform

- **Sign out:** Log out of the browser session

## Scene and pop-up sidebar
The sidebar contains a palette of individual scenes and pop-ups, with action buttons to manage them.

![User interface displaying scenes and popups for a digital project management tool.](data:image/png;base64,)Scene sidebar with a scene and a pop-up

- The **plus button** instantly adds a new scene to the palette.

- To add a pop-up, expand the **arrow menu** and click **New pop-up**.

- Hover over a scene or pop-up and click the **edit button** to open the **scene editor**.

- Click the **three-dot menu** below the thumbnail and select one of the options - **Duplicate **or **Delete**.

## Storyboard editor
The Storyboard editor is the plotting area where individual scenes and pop-ups from the sidebar can be added and connected to form a full interactive video flow. These actions can be performed using intuitive drag-and-drop controls.

![Storyboard interface displaying an untitled scene with a play button for video playback.](data:image/png;base64,)

> Tip: Getting started with Video Designer

The entire editing process can be seen in action in [Getting started: Create a Pvideo with Video Designer](/doxee-platform/docs/pvideo-designer-getting-started).

## User actions in the Project editor
The following actions can be performed from the Storyboard editor:

- **Create or duplicate a scene or pop-up**

- **Delete a scene or pop-up**

- **Open the scene editor**

- **Add and connect scenes on the Storyboard**
